Package com.ezasm.assembler

Record Class Directive.WriteRInstruction

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Record
com.ezasm.assembler.Directive.WriteRInstruction
Record Components:
function - the MIPS function number.
sourceLeft - the left source register number. This may not actually be on the left depending on the instruction.
sourceRight - the right source register number. This may not actually be on the right depending on the instruction.
dest - the destination register number.
shift - the shift amount for bit shift instructions. This value 0 for all other instructions.
All Implemented Interfaces:
Directive
Enclosing interface:
Directive
public static record Directive.WriteRInstruction(byte function, byte sourceLeft, byte sourceRight, byte dest, byte shift) extends Record implements Directive
A Directive that writes a MIPS instruction in the current section of an Assembler instance using the MIPS Register encoding.
